    "name": "Sotetsu Fresa Inn Seoul Myeong-dong",
    "detail": "The best thing of this hotel is its location within the shopping district of Myeong-dong. Decent accessibility from both Euljiro-1 and Myeong-dong station could allow you to enjoy ultimate shopping and dining experiences despite the fact that the area is somewhat touristy to me. It's still a very good option for first-time visitors. Our room was very clean and neat, plus well-equipped with most things you could find in typical midscale Japanese hotels. The price was very reasonable considering what we were provided. Easy & quick check-in/out process. The only downside that I can come up with is that it might be difficult to take a taxi right in front of the hotel's door because it is a shopping street where roads are dedicated to pedestrians during day & night. Could be inconvenient for the elders or those who're not keen on walking.",
